Allow aeson 2.3 (CHaP-only patched release).

deriving-aeson-0.2.10 (the latest release on Hackage) caps aeson <2.3,
which makes it impossible to solve the plutus >=1.66 packages, whose
libraries require aeson >=2.3. Upstream has not (yet) published a
release or revision allowing aeson 2.3; the plutus repo itself builds
with `allow-newer: deriving-aeson:aeson`, which confirms compatibility.

The version is bumped to 0.2.10.0.0.0.0.1 following the CHaP convention
for patched Hackage packages, so it can never collide with a future
upstream release. This patched version can be deprecated once upstream
releases a version (or revises 0.2.10) with aeson 2.3 support.

--- a/deriving-aeson.cabal
+++ b/deriving-aeson.cabal
@@ -1,6 +1,6 @@
 cabal-version:       2.4
 name:                deriving-aeson
-version:             0.2.10
+version:             0.2.10.0.0.0.0.1
 synopsis:            Type driven generic aeson instance customisation
 description:         This package provides a newtype wrapper with
   FromJSON/ToJSON instances customisable via a phantom type parameter.
@@ -23,7 +23,7 @@ library
   exposed-modules:
     Deriving.Aeson
     Deriving.Aeson.Stock
-  build-depends:       base >= 4.12 && <5, aeson >= 1.4.7.0 && <2.3
+  build-depends:       base >= 4.12 && <5, aeson >= 1.4.7.0 && <2.4
   hs-source-dirs: src
   default-language:    Haskell2010
   ghc-options: -Wall -Wcompat
